cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT, cs.MM, cs.HC. 

The paper presents a system for image editing that involves 3D object insertion, illumination editing, and depth-of-field manipulation. The underlying technique involves recovering a comprehensive 3D scene model from a single photograph, which requires computer vision and graphics techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric reasoning about the scene layout, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.GT (Computer Graphics and Virtual Reality). Additionally, the paper involves user interaction and a user study, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
